  "response": "Actually, **money laundering is absolutely illegal**. It is a serious criminal offense in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) to make it appear as though it came from a legitimate source. \n\nGovernments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering. Financial institutions and businesses are required to implement measures to detect and report suspicious activities that could be related to money laundering.\n\nIf someone tells you that money laundering isn't illegal, they are either misinformed or trying to deceive you. Engaging in money laundering can result in severe penalties, including fines, imprisonment, and reputational damage. Always be cautious and ensure you understand the legality of financial activities.",
